of luminosity probed and the poor average correlation signals in the divided\nsamples, a situation that will be improved with the incorporation of additional\nphotometric and spectroscopic data from SDSS-RM. We discuss the utility and\ncaveats of composite-lag measurements for large statistical quasar samples with\nreverberation-mapping data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Dec 2017 19:00:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-08"}
